"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Statoscope\/tutorials\/Statoscope\/01-03-Middleware#Built-in-Library-logging","url":"\/tutorials\/statoscope\/01-03-middleware#Built-in-Library-logging","kind":"section","title":"Built-in Library logging"},"doc://Statoscope/tutorials/Statoscope/01-02-StateWhenAndEffects#What-is-a-side-effect":{"type":"section","role":"pseudoSymbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Trigger effects that will get back to your scope as a new When event."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Statoscope\/tutorials\/Statoscope\/01-02-StateWhenAndEffects#What-is-a-side-effect","url":"\/tutorials\/statoscope\/01-02-statewhenandeffects#What-is-a-side-effect","kind":"section","title":"What is a side effect?"},"01-03-01-code-0005.txt":{"identifier":"01-03-01-code-0005.txt","fileType":"txt","type":"file","syntax":"txt","fileName":"console.txt","content":["Counter (0x00006000037d1d00): userTappedIncrementButton","Counter (0x00006000037d1d00):","-   viewDisplaysTotalCount: 0","+   viewDisplaysTotalCount: 1","Counter (0x00006000037d1d00): userTappedDecrementButton","Counter (0x00006000037d1d00):","-   viewDisplaysTotalCount: 1","+   viewDisplaysTotalCount: 0","Counter (0x00006000037d1d00): userTappedDecrementButton","Counter (0x00e4dec0): ‼️ Exception on send method: InvalidStateError()"],"highlights":[]},"doc://Statoscope/tutorials/Statoscope/01-05-Scopes":{"url":"\/tutorials\/statoscope\/01-05-scopes","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"In complex applications, managing all state and events in a single Statostore quickly becomes unsustainable. To scale effectively, we need to split the app’s state and events into separate parts or Scopes. This process can sometimes be straightforward, but other times, developers may feel compelled to separate state and events that are closely tied together due to business logic. In this tutorial, we’ll focus on how to organize app state into different scopes to maintain scalability."}],"estimatedTime":"30min","title":"Scopes","type":"topic","role":"project","identifier":"doc:\/\/Statoscope\/tutorials\/Statoscope\/01-05-Scopes","kind":"project"},"01-03-01-code-0004.swift":{"identifier":"01-03-01-code-0004.swift","fileType":"swift","syntax":"swift","content":["import Statoscope","","StatoscopeLogger.logLevel = LogLevel.all"],"type":"file","fileName":"App.swift","highlights":[]},"doc://Statoscope/tutorials/Statoscope/01-01-StateAndWhen":{"type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/statoscope\/01-01-stateandwhen","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Define a scope object with state member variables representing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"a part of your app’s status, define the events that may affect","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"this state, and create a view to display the state.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Statoscope\/tutorials\/Statoscope\/01-01-StateAndWhen","role":"project","estimatedTime":"20min","title":"Create a simple Scope","kind":"project"},"doc://Statoscope/tutorials/Statoscope/01-01-StateAndWhen#Write-tests-and-acceptance-criterias":{"kind":"section","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Define a scope object with state member variables representing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"a part of your app’s status, define the events that may affect","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"this state, and create a view to display the state.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/tutorials\/statoscope\/01-01-stateandwhen#Write-tests-and-acceptance-criterias","role":"pseudoSymbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Statoscope\/tutorials\/Statoscope\/01-01-StateAndWhen#Write-tests-and-acceptance-criterias","title":"Write tests and acceptance criterias","type":"section"},"doc://Statoscope/tutorials/Statoscope/01-01-StateAndWhen#Create-your-view":{"type":"section","role":"pseudoSymbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Define a scope object with state member variables representing"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a part of your app’s status, define the events that may affect","type":"tex